This gene plays a role in both transcription and anterior/posterior axis formation.

Human HOXA3 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 7p15.2 and is approximately 46 kb in length. This allele, which encodes homeobox protein Hox-A3, is involved in both pattern formation and the regulation of gene expression.
A microscopic finding indicating that a tumor exhibits more than one line of histologic differentiation.
Homeobox protein Hox-A3 (443 aa, ~46 kDa) is encoded by the human HOXA3 gene. This protein plays a role in both the modulation of gene expression and anterior/posterior embryonic patterning.
This gene is involved in the modulation of embryonic gene expression.

Human HOXB6 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 17q21.32 and is approximately 11 kb in length. This allele, which encodes homeobox protein Hox-B6, plays a role in transcription of patterning genes.
Homeobox protein Hox-B6 (224 aa, ~25 kDa) is encoded by the human HOXB6 gene. This protein is involved in embryonic pattern formation.
This gene plays a role in protein folding.

Human HSPD1 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 2q33.1 and is approximately 30 kb in length. This allele, which encodes 60 kDa heat shock protein, mitochondrial, is involved in both import and folding of mitochondrial proteins. Mutation of the gene is associated with spastic paraplegia 13 and leukodystrophy hypomyelinating type 4.
60 kDa heat shock protein, mitochondrial (573 aa, ~61 kDa) is encoded by the human HSPD1 gene. This protein plays a role in mitochondrial protein folding.
This gene is involved in cytokine signaling.

Human IL20 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 1q32 and is approximately 4 kb in length. This allele, which encodes interleukin-20 protein, plays a role in cytokine signaling through activation of signal transducer and activator of transcription 3.
Interleukin-20 (176 aa, ~20 kDa) is encoded by the human IL20 gene. This protein is involved in the regulation of signal transducer and activator of transcription 3-mediated signaling.
This gene plays a role in both cytokine signaling and immune responses.
Human IL21 wild-type allele is located within 4q26-q27 and is approximately 8 kb in length. This allele, which encodes interleukin-21 protein, is involved in both immunity and signaling.
Interleukin-21 (155 aa, ~18 kDa) is encoded by the human IL21 gene. This protein plays a role in both receptor-mediated signaling and the inflammatory response.
This gene is involved in both immunomodulation and antiviral responses.

Human IFNL2 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 19q13.13 and is approximately 2 kb in length. This allele, which encodes interferon lambda-2 protein, plays a role in both the response to viral infection and cytokine signaling.
Interferon lambda-2 (200 aa, ~22 kDa) is encoded by the human IFNL2 gene. This protein is involved in both cytokine-mediated signaling and antiviral activity.
This gene plays a role in both the antiviral response and signaling.

Human IFNL1 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 19q13.13 and is approximately 2 kb in length. This allele, which encodes interferon lambda-1 protein, is involved in both cytokine-dependent signaling and host defense.
Interferon lambda-1 (200 aa, ~22 kDa) is encoded by the human IFNL1 gene. This protein plays a role in both cytokine signaling and the response to viral infection.

Human GZMB wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 14q11.2 and is approximately 3 kb in length. This allele, which encodes granzyme B protein, is involved in both proteolysis and cellular immune responses.

label.value: European Organization for Research and Treatment of Cancer Quality of Life Questionnaire Core 30

value.value: A 30-item questionnaire about patient ability to function, symptoms related to the cancer and its treatment, overall health and quality of life, and perceived financial impact of cancer and its treatment.
This gene is involved in microtubule dynamics.

Human KIF2C wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 1p34.1 and is approximately 28 kb in length. This allele, which encodes kinesin-like protein KIF2C, plays a role in the regulation of microtubule depolymerization.
Kinesin-like protein KIF2C (725 aa, ~81 kDa) is encoded by the human KIF2C gene. This protein is involved in tubulin depolymerization.
This gene plays a role in natural killer cell activity.

Human KIR3DL1 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 19q13.4 and is approximately 142 kb in length. This allele, which encodes killer cell immunoglobulin-like receptor 3DL1 protein, is involved in the regulation of natural killer cell activity.
Killer cell immunoglobulin-like receptor 3DL1 (444 aa, ~49 kDa) is encoded by the human KIR3DL1 gene. This protein plays a role in the modulation of cell-mediated cytotoxicity.
This gene is involved in the regulation of immune responses.

Human KLRC1 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 12p13 and is approximately 12 kb in length. This allele, which encodes NKG2-A/NKG2-B type II integral membrane protein, plays a role in the regulation of immune signaling pathways.

label.value: NKG2-A/NKG2-B Type II Integral Membrane Protein

value.value: NKG2-A/NKG2-B type II integral membrane protein (233 aa, ~26 kDa) is encoded by the human KLRC1 gene. This protein is involved in the modulation of cell-mediated immunity.
